HEADWORD: Thermoluminescence
<hw>Ther`mo*lu`mi*nes"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Luminescence exhibited by a substance on being
moderately heated. It is shown esp. by certain substances that have been
exposed to the action of light or to X-rays.</def><-- ##?? used in
dating of pottery? --> -- <wordforms><wf>Ther`mo*lu`mi*nes"cent</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

